Hey @everyone, quick thought and question!

I wanted to start a conversation about how we’re handling daily posts. Right now, we’re following the daily theme schedule, but if everyone posts a separate topic each day, it feels like there’s a lot of content going out — and not as much back-and-forth conversation as we had on the WhatsApp group.

We’ve also heard feedback from the WhatsApp group that there’s already so much content it’s hard to stay on top of everything, and I’m wondering if the way we’re posting now might actually exacerbate that feeling.

Maybe we could try limiting it to 5 posts per day (either first-come, first-post, or assigning 5 people per day) and focusing more on fueling deeper conversations around those posts, rather than prioritizing a lot of content?

It also seems like the themes might be overwhelming people — instead of casually sharing interesting ideas, they might feel like they have to perfectly fit the theme. I’m wondering if the structure could unintentionally make non-leaders feel more shy about jumping in.

Also — slight meta question — is this even the right place to be posting this? 😅 Feels like even figuring out where to bring these kinds of discussions is part of what we’re learning as we go.

Curious what you all think!
